summary: RVDelaysec configured vs default delay with user interruption
description: |
    Tests directive delay behavior with unreachable rendezvous endpoints:
    - First directive fails TO1 with configured 5s delay
    - Second (last) directive fails TO1, triggering default 120s delay
    - SIGINT sent to verify graceful user cancellation
    - Validates "Onboarding canceled by user" message

test: ./test-retry-rvdelaysec-vs-default.sh

framework: shell

duration: 10m

require:
  - go-fdo-server
  - go-fdo-server-manufacturer
  - go-fdo-server-owner
  - go-fdo-server-rendezvous

tag:
  - fdo
  - e2e
  - protocol
  - retry
  - delay
  - rpm
  - server
